Prepare and heat ham according to package directions. Meanwhile, prepare glaze. In small saucepan, combine lemon juice, orange juice, brown sugar, margarine and cinnamon; bring to boil. Boil 1 minute. Reduce heat; add apple and orange and simmer 2-3 minutes. Brush glaze on your Cook's ham 30 minutes before meat is done. Heat ham uncovered for final 30 minutes. Carve ham and serve.